<section
  id="about"
  class="relative z-10 border-t border-[color-mix(in_srgb,var(--color-accent)_8%,var(--color-border))] bg-canvas py-24 md:py-32"
  aria-labelledby="about-heading"
>
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute left-[8%] top-0 h-px w-[30%] max-w-md bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-accent/25 to-transparent md:left-[12%]" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6" data-reveal>
    <p
      class="mono mb-10 text-center text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-accent/90 md:text-xs"
    >
      Why I Build This
    </p>
    <h2 id="about-heading" class="sr-only">About</h2>
    <div
      class="relative rounded-2xl border border-[color-mix(in_srgb,var(--color-accent)_10%,var(--color-border))] bg-[color-mix(in_srgb,var(--color-surface)_35%,transparent)] px-6 py-10 shadow-[0_20px_60px_rgba(0,0,0,0.35)] backdrop-blur-[2px] md:px-12 md:py-12"
    >
      <div
        class="pointer-events-none absolute bottom-8 left-5 top-8 w-px bg-gradient-to-b from-accent/40 via-accent/15 to-transparent md:left-8"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-7 pl-5 text-[17px] leading-[1.75] text-text-primary/95 md:pl-8 md:text-[17.5px] md:leading-[1.8]">
        <p>
          After years working across financial services, aviation, telecom, and healthcare, I kept
          running into the same structural problems: security added at the end, findings without
          context, tools that generated noise instead of clarity, and teams with no practical path to
          improve.
        </p>
        <p>
          I started building the tools I wished had existed. Not platforms designed for enterprise
          sales cycles, but practical, open-source tooling built for teams that actually need to ship
          secure software without a dedicated security department for every service.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each project here came from a real problem I encountered or observed directly. The goal is
          always the same: reduce friction, increase visibility, and make security something teams want
          to integrate, not avoid.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
